resources.string: Sanca is a common name for all types of constrictors classified as the family Pythonidae. Sanca is widespread in the hot and tropical climates of Africa, Asia, and Australia. One of the sanca species, the sanca kembang is the longest snake in the world
Anacondas are a group of large snakes that are endemic in freshwater and rivers in tropical South America

Lampropeltis is the name of a genus of collubrid snake found in America. Its scientific name, Lampropeltis luminous scales comes from the words Lampros light and shield pelt, referring to their glossy skin scales.

Mamba is the general name for four species of deadly venomous snakes which are all classified as the genus Dendroaspis. These snakes are endemic to the African continent and some of their species have earned the reputation of being the deadliest snakes in the world

The worm, which has the Latin name Trichuris trichiura, has a length of 5 cm in females and 4 cm in males. This worm lives in the large intestine and when it becomes an adult worm will stick to the wall of the small intestine and suck blood. Usually it will cause abdominal pain, decreased appetite, and anemia
